cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new processor design that provides secure enclaves under a threat model that includes an untrusted OS and an attacker capable of mounting any software attack currently considered practical. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is also likely as the paper proposes a new processor design that extends the isolation guarantee to more realistic memory hierarchies. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of enclaves on program performance and models it through FPGA emulation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new instruction, the purge instruction, and implements it for a complex processor microarchitecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new processor design that provides secure enclaves and models its performance impact.
